document_data.History:
Trobriand was an ex-student of Halaster Blackcloak. Although he was a powerful mage in his own right, Trobriand did not pose a threat to Halaster himself.

For a time, Trobriand acted as guildmaster of the [[Hands of Time]], a mechanics' guild and shop in [[Sigil]]'s [[Sigil/Lower Ward|Lower Ward]]. He was later succeeded in this position by his student, [[Saddam Hasan ibn Arvalas]].

Trobriand, together with [[Muiral]], created an arcane academy in the upper levels of Undermountain, gathering a group of spellcasters called [[Halaster's Heirs]]. After Halaster's death in [[1375 DR]], Trobriand planned to seize total control of the dungeon, but before he could act, the [[Spellplague]] hit in [[1385 DR]], after which the Metal Mage disappeared.{{Cite dungeon/201/Trobriand's Machinations|1}}
